ScalarVariable.name: step.startTime
ScalarVariable.description: Output y = offset for time < startTime

ScalarVariable.name: G4HIL.__recalibrated
ScalarVariable.description: Signals whether the eFMU has been recalibrated before calling 'DoStep()'\n or not.

ScalarVariable.name: G4HIL.__error_signals_Recalibrate
ScalarVariable.description: Error signals returned throughout the execution of the 'Recalibrate()'\n function of the defining production code.

ScalarVariable.name: G4HIL.__error_signals_Reinitialize
ScalarVariable.description: Error signals returned throughout the execution of the 'Reinitialize()'\n function of the defining production code.

ScalarVariable.name: G4HIL.__error_signals_DoStep
ScalarVariable.description: Error signals returned throughout the execution of the 'DoStep()'\n function of the defining production code.

ScalarVariable.name: G4HIL.__assert_error_signals
ScalarVariable.description: Configures if error signals of the defining production code are asserted\n or not.

ScalarVariable.name: G4HIL.__embedd_clock
ScalarVariable.description:
Configures the synchronous integration of the stub; whether it defines
 such itself (i.e., has its own clock; '__embedd_clock = true') or uses the
 clock of its instanciation context (i.e., uses an external clock;
 '__embedd_clock = false').

ScalarVariable.name: G4HIL.__sampling_period
ScalarVariable.description: Configures the sampling period of the stub. In case of an embedded clock\n ('__embedd_clock = true') its sampling period and in case of an external\n clock the expected sampling period of such as required by the eFMU.

ScalarVariable.name: G4HIL.__enable_tuning
ScalarVariable.description: Configures if tuning via the tuning bus is supported or not.

ScalarVariable.name: G4HIL.__enable_reinitialization
ScalarVariable.description: Configures if reinitialization is supported or not; if enabled, runtime\n values for the '__reinitialize' input must be provided.

ScalarVariable.name: G4HIL.__sampled.__recalibrate
ScalarVariable.description: Support variable used to decide if a recalibration of eFMU production\n codes is required before executing their 'DoStep()' implementation.

ScalarVariable.name: G4HIL.__sampled.__reinitialize
ScalarVariable.description: Support variable used to decide if a reinitialization of eFMU production\n codes is requested before executing their 'DoStep()' implementation.

ScalarVariable.name: G4HIL.__sampled.fault
ScalarVariable.description: Fault input sigal, default false = fault inactive

ScalarVariable.name: G4HIL.__is_initialized
ScalarVariable.description:
Support variable used to ensure correct initialization of eFMU production
 codes right before the first 'DoStep()' call (e.g., tuneables parameters
 are correctly recalibrated according to modifications of the stub instance,
 states are initialized using the inputs at the first clock tick etc).

ScalarVariable.name: G4HIL.fault
ScalarVariable.description: Fault input sigal, default false = fault inactive

ScalarVariable.name: G4HIL.__defining_code
ScalarVariable.description: The production code defining the stub's results,\n i.e., whose results are propagated by the stub.

ScalarVariable.name: G4HIL.__active_codes[1]
ScalarVariable.description: Set of production codes co-simulated. By default, all production codes\n are co-simulated. The '__defining_code' is always active, even if not\n explicitly listed in the set.

ScalarVariable.name: G4HIL.__active_codes[2]
